    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">My second version of the deck i play. First one may be seeing here:<br />
<br />
http://decktech.net/lotr/decks/decks.php?deck=34290<br />
<br />
In that page, i explained the deck widely, so here, i only explain the difference.<br />
<br />
<br />
First, i change the RB. Now i use PbM, because you are going to bid high, and Frodo must die before Enquea was seen. You´ll transfer the ring to Sam, who is a big RB, with 5 resistance, but the advantage of Sting removing burdens. In adition, you may exert Frodo to muster, and get Farmer Maggot as soon as possible. You have 2 Farmers. If you don´t get early, at least, you can pathfind (with map) to get Green dragon inn. Bafore you play Maggot, you must assure kill Frodo, to avoid Enquea.<br />
<br />
Second, with Sam removing burdens, you may remove a Good work. i keep one becouse it´s great agains corruption.<br />
<br />
The adding of one Rosie Cotton is obvious. Heal Sam for 1, and give strengh to your RB. I keep the Gaffer because is heal a wound for 1.<br />
<br />
One important change are Aragorn´s toys. I need some slots, so, i remove the bow and the sword, and play Anduril, FotW. It gives more vitality to Aragorn and more pathfind. With that, i can remove one Thror´s map.<br />
<br />
One Everyone knows is cutting to save a slot. In spite of it, you have enough tales to Bilbo works. And i add one Hobbit intuition more. You may change for a Birthday present.<br />
<br />
I don´t add more companions because your guys wouldn´t have to die easily.<br />
<br />
Again, Unharmed may be good, but i don´t find room for it.<br />
<br />
<br />
I hope this deck likes like the other. <br />
<br />
Happy new year to all.<br />
